.Dd $Mdocdate: April 9 2018 $
.Dt KHTTP_FCGI_PARSE 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm khttp_fcgi_parse
.Nd parse a FastCGI instance for kcgi
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libkcgi
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/types.h
.In stdarg.h
.In stdint.h
.In kcgi.h
.Ft "enum kcgi_err"
.Fo khttp_fcgi_parse
.Fa "struct kfcgi *fcgi"
.Fa "struct kreq *req"
.Fc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn khttp_fcgi_parse
function parses and validates a single FastCGI request.
They may be invoked as many times as necessary, but must follow a call
to
.Xr khttp_fcgi_init 3
and be followed by
.Xr khttp_fcgi_free 3 .
.Pp
The
.Fa req
object filled in by
.Fn khttp_fcgi_parse
must be matched by
.Xr khttp_free 3
if and only if the return value is
.Dv KCGI_OK .
Otherwise, resources are internally freed.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
These are the same as in
.Xr khttp_parse 3 ,
except the
.Dv KCGI_EXIT
return code indicates that no more requests will arrive and the
application should exit.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kcgi 3 ,
.Xr khttp_fcgi_init 3 ,
.Xr khttp_free 3 ,
.Xr khttp_parse 3
.Sh AUTHORS
The
.Fn khttp_fcgi_parse
function was written by
